cafes.name: Right Meow Cat Cafe
cafes.address: 913 S Main St, Fuquay-Varina, NC 27526, USA

text.text: Brought my daughter and friends here for her birthday.  Was an adorable place, super well done.  Decor was fabulous, cats were lovely and atmosphere is tranquil.  They also serve beverages.  I'm guessing we will be coming back!  Love the mission of the place for adopting cats and finding them forever homes!

Lovely and unique cafe! We made a last minute reservation online. As suggested, we arrived 10 minutes early to park and order our drinks (highly recommend arriving early!). The place was immaculate. It was very clean and free of odors. I‚Äôm not a cat person (my daughter is though- hence why we went!), and I fell in love with cats right there and then.
You can really tell they care about the safety and wellbeing on the cats. They‚Äôre all very clean and healthy. The place is calm and welcoming for both cats and humans. The cats have a large variety of places to go play, hide, sleep, etc., and cat toys are available in every room. We loved reading about each cat and getting to know them all. We were even given treats to feed the cats. The drinks were great, and my daughter tried the (‚Äúvery artistic‚Äù) red velvet cakepop. A friendly staff member kept coming in to check in and answer any questions. If we ever decide to adopt a cat, this would be the only place we would adopt from.

We love this place!! It has awesome drinks and booking time with the kitties is so special. You can tell the priority is the well being of the cats because they have so many amazing places throughout for them to hide and get out of reach if they are not feeling people-y. You will not find a cleaner establishment. (And if you didn't know, all the cats are up for adoption! Sadly we cannot due to allergies in the family but we love to go and support them).

I had a fantastic time at Purr Cup Cafe! The cats are very healthy and well taken care of, which made the experience even more enjoyable. The setup is great, providing a perfect environment to play and relax with the kitties. Plus, the coffee was excellent! Highly recommend this place for any cat lover.

This is such a cute little cafe! Went to see the cats and had a great time + bought some cute cat-related items for cat lovers I know. Lots of cute merchandise! Hats, shirts, pins, cards, etc. you‚Äôll definitely find something cute for someone who loves cats! Check it out!

The cats were also friendly and curious when we went, especially the orange cat, Chives! He thought he was the king in the castle üè∞ and owner of the cafe üòÄ. Full of personality! If you are looking to adopt a cat, definitely check this place out and maybe you‚Äôll be lucky enough to meet Chives while there ü•∞. He was up for adoption too!

Each time slots 1 hour. Plenty of time to finish your drinks and pet/play with the cats! The cats like the really fluffy toy that looked like bird feathers. If you shake it real fast, cats get very into it (maybe thinking it‚Äôs a fluttering bird ü¶ÖüòÄ)!

I wish there was a larger waiting room area. We arrived kind of early and there‚Äôs just one table with 2 chairs in the waiting room. But the place is tiny, so I understand the space constrains. You can always wait outside on the porch or look around for cute merchandise.

By the way, I got a lavender matcha tea at the cafe and it was excellent! Unusual taste, which I really enjoyed!

The place is LGBTQ-friendly and has lots of pride merchandise.

Purr Cafe is amazing!! What a wonderful place. Coffee + kitties? Yes please. The kitties are adorable and lots of fun to be around. There are lots of toys for the cats and tons of joy all around. The atmosphere is excellent and the service is top notch. We were fortunate enough to be well taken care of by Nia and Leif on our visit this weekend. Thank you both so much for making us feel so welcome and raising our experience level even more by your thoughtfulness!

Good coffee, too. Fun merch available. Definitely a must visit if in the area and you like cats and or coffee!

cafes.name: Bad Cat Coffee, Crepes, & Bagel Sammiches
cafes.address: 411 W Morgan St, Raleigh, NC 27603, USA

text.text: Service and Atmosphere are five stars, I love the vibe. However the only reason I did four stars for the food is because the coffee does taste a bit bitter and coffee cake too sweet. However, the crepe was amazing. Absolutely amazing. Check them out!

This is like trail magic on a Saturday morning. Super friendly, fun staff that bring a smile to the start of your day. The coffee lattes are great and I had a sausage, egg and cheese burrito that hit the spot. This is inside the Morgan Street food Hall with plenty of space to grab a seat and stay warm on a chilly winter morning. Thank you for the good vibes!

My wife and I came to Raleigh for my Wife's birthday and this was one of thd places she wanted to try. She saw an Instagram post and sent it to me.

She got the berries n cream crepe and I got the smores crepe. Both were amazing. We also got the P.Purr latte and the Hairball latte. Again, amazing.

The food court in general has a phenomenal atmosphere. 10/10 highly recommend.

This place is adorable! We made a reservation as a pit stop while on a day trip, and it was amazing! The cats were adorable and fun to be around, the food was good, and the owners were so kind! Highly recommend if you‚Äôre in the area!

We had a great time visiting with the cats and kittens . I ordered an ice coffee and it was delicious !!! My kids ordered a smoothie and enjoyed it as well. The owners are super nice . Will be back for sure
This place is phenomenal!! 13/10 recommend! The owners are amazing and the kitties are so stinking cute! If you have time, this is a great place to relax and have your stress melt away!

cafes.name: Mac Tabby Cat Cafe - Charlotte
cafes.address: 3204 N Davidson St, Charlotte, NC 28205, USA

text.text:
Such a great place and I have to say the staff do such a good job taking care of the cats. The cats seem so happy, well fed, and playful.

The coffee was great as well!! I got the brown sugar oat latte. It was perfect. Very sweet though - if that‚Äôs not your thing.

Cute cats + great coffee? We even did cat tarot card readings üêà‚Äç‚¨õ. It was a phenomenal time.

I had so much fun here. The woman working the counter was so nice. Their decor was super cute. The best part of course was the cats. I had the best time playing with them. Especially their two senior cats they have right now.

We flew into Charlotte in the morning and were looking for things to do until we could check into our hotel. We found Mac Tabby and easily made a reservation.When we arrived, we were greeted by a staff member and escorted to the cat room. It was great! There were other people in the room, but it wasn‚Äôt crowded at all. There were plenty of places to sit and many interactive toys to play with. It was clean and the cats were well cared for. They had places to climb and they could get away from the humans if they wanted to. All the cats were so sweet and playful. The hour went way too quickly! If we find ourselves in Charlotte again, we‚Äôll definitely be back!

I was actually quite surprised how good the coffee  and food was here and with decent pricing considering it is in the NODA area. My husband and I ordered a Dirty Chai, A latte, a biscuit, bagel and breakfast for Burrito all for $35.

You do have to ordered through an iPad yourself at a self order kiosk station which you may or may not like. It luckily wasn‚Äôt busy and had to wait long, but I can definitely see getting annoyed with people in front of you ordering and taking forever not knowing how to use an iPad ordering system and have multiple things to order. After you order they then will call out your name at the next window to the left of the kiosk station.

Either way, I definitely would come back here again because of the quality of the coffee and food were really good in my opinion.

I wanted to like Smelly Cat more than I did. While the coffee and food was great, the service experience was very subpar. Not only was ordering done on iPads but you then had to wait 20+ minutes by the pick up window. If they expect that sort of wait, a better pickup system needs to be in place, whether it be a text or buzzer. Rather than spend time with my friends, I had to spend 15 minutes waiting for my bagel and then another 15 waiting for my cappuccino.

We‚Äôre just visiting Charlotte for the weekend and found this place & are so glad we did! The owner was more than accommodating- she explained the menu and even suggested samples before we ordered to make sure we got coffee that we really enjoyed! She went above and beyond to make sure our experience was excellent. They make all of their syrups and even roast their own coffee! The inside has a few tables and does have AC, she does lock the front door though always so just order at the window first and she will give you a table inside if you‚Äôd like, or there are lots of spaces outside to sit too! I had the lavender cold brew and it was delicious. My friend who came with got a decaf latte with spiced brown sugar syrup (which was homemade) & that was fantastic too! They also have some Cuban coffee that I would love to give a try too! We didn‚Äôt order food, but would‚Äôve gotten a bagel, frittata (only served on weekends), donut, or sandwich. Highly recommend this cozy, welcoming coffee shop!

Visited at 11:30am, because we arrived downtown thirty minutes before our appointment and needed a place to appreciate Life and Living. The Heart warming energy of the resident Cats is wonderful. Highly recommended, bring a partner, friend, date. If you really Love cats, get closer right here.

I have just moved out to Asheville, walking around the area I wasn't looking for a cat cafe, but the second I saw it I knew I had to check it out. First the aesthetic of this Cafe is amazing, beautiful design that makes it feel like it was made for the cats, and for the people of Asheville. The employees were very friendly and helpful when it came to understanding how the cafe worked and what all can be done here. I grabbed a drink, which regrettably I don't remember the name of as it was a long day, and throughly enjoy it! Once I got to hang out with the cats I felt such joy, not being able to have a cat at the moment this was the perfect opportunity to experience being around them again. All of them were very sweet and the kittens were adorable to see and play with. I will be coming back here to enjoy the Cafe and experience they offer!

What a cute and cute wonderful place! Offers coffee, tea, beers, wine, while you play with kitties. Adorably decorated and VERY clean - no kitty smell at all! $12pp for 30 min got you access to 2 rooms. One with older cats and one for kittens. Buy a tube of treats for $1 and you‚Äôll get lots of attention! Kitties are for adoption and they seem to have helped over 150 cats get homes since the start of the year. This is my new retirement plan LOL

cafes.name: Frabjous Catfe
cafes.address: 12261 Capital Blvd, Wake Forest, NC 27587, USA

text.text: Such a beautiful and welcoming little gem! My sister took me there for some matcha and chai. The girls at the counter were very welcoming, took our orders and answered all of my questions (I tend to ask a lot)‚Ä¶. I love that they showcase artwork from local artists! I  did not get to see or interact with any cats but that‚Äôs okay‚Ä¶ I‚Äôll be back!

I was blown away with this place!  From the friendly and helpful staff to the delicious drinks and cupcakes to the cats, this place definitely deserves way more than just 5 stars!  As someone that rents a home and unable to have cats, this is the best place to go and get my cat fix!  The cats were all super friendly especially with my 9 year old and they literally had everything you could ever need including a lint roller you can use if needed on the way out.  We cannot wait to go back!

I love a good coffee shop & this one also has Kitty cats! Bonus! I have visited the kitty room to pet the kitties. I'd take them all home if I didn't already have 2 at home. I recently attended Yoga with Cori in the kitty room & it made all my dreams come true! I think I'll be a regular here. :)

cafes.name: Crooked Tail Cat Cafe
cafes.address: 604 S Elm St, Greensboro, NC 27406, USA

text.text: Cute cute cute! My first time at a cat cafe, loved the cat themed drinks and the cat boba cups! All of the kitty cats were adorable, didn‚Äôt get the chance to play with them this time but definitely next time. Their gift shop has a bunch of cat themed items. Overall as a cat person I was over the moon!
This was such a cute place! It was fun learning about the cats and seeing their personalities.  It was very clean, and the cats seemed well taken care of. We would love to visit again one day!

We loved going here and the atmosphere was great!! The cats were playful and curious, very great friends.The drinks they had were great and no kitties knocked over any drinks. I can‚Äôt wait to come back here again!!

cafes.name: Mac Tabby Cat Cafe - Concord
cafes.address: 25 Market St SW, Concord, NC 28025, USA

text.text: Had the most amazing time here today! The staff were very friendly and patient, coffee was done quick and it was really delicious. I would come here for just the drinks. Hanging with the kitties was also amazing. They were all so chill and it's really fun to watch them all interact with each other/do their own things. There's something therapeutic about being in such a cozy environment with so many kitties. Will definitely be coming back, absolutely worth the 40 minute drive :)

A MUST visit if you loveeee cats üêà ‚òï Coffee, latte, smoothies, beer/wine üç∑ The kitties are all adoptable, yall! Come experience this place. The ambience is so inviting and extremely clean. Outdoor patio with string lights and patio heater /fans. You know you want a great drink and pet the sweetest funniest cats. üòç Solid 10/10

Phenomenal place! The staff were friendly, the place itself was inviting, and the cats were adorable. It's 10$ for half an hour and 14$ for an hour in the cat lounge, and the coffees are about 4.50$ on average. I tried a coffee and a cream soda and both were delicious. Drinks were allowed into the cat lounge. They had seasonal flavors for coffee, and the cafe was decorated very nicely for the holiday season. The cat room itself was spacious, with a variety of cat toys to use. There was a TV in the corner of the room that played a slideshow with images and names of the cats, and all of the cats are listed online as well. Overall it was an amazing experience and I'll be sure to visit again when I'm in town.

cafes.name: Cat Tales Cat Cafe
cafes.address: 431 W Franklin St, Chapel Hill, NC 27516, USA

text.text: Great place that takes care of cats - and allows people (for a fee) an hour to play with and pet the cats. There were about 9 of them when we went. You can buy drinks and get ice cream when you get in. Some cats wanted to be petted and would purr; others wanted to play and there were many toys. We spent the whole hour and it went by quickly. The cats are meant to be adopted.

Such a wonderful Cat Cafe and a great experience! The cats are obviously well cared for, the place was very clean, and it was a very relaxed atmosphere to visit the kitties. There were about seven of us in the location, and it never seemed crowded. The person helping at the front desk was very knowledgeable and patient with everyone, and they had a lot of cute things to shop for as well. Would definitely recommend this place!

An amazing place! Employees were so kind in helping me find a cat to adopt and very communicative during the transition period of bringing her home. The cafe itself is very clean and entertaining for cats and people with plenty of well cared for and well socialized cats. Cannot recommend this place enough!

cafes.name: Mac Tabby Cat Cafe - Salisbury
cafes.address: 103 S Main St, Salisbury, NC 28144, USA

text.text: First time at a cat cafe. Bought an hour for my wife and I to hang out Valentine‚Äôs Day. Cool place. All the cats are adoptable. Have a latte and pet some cats. Nice relaxing experience and the money goes to care for the cats. 1900+ adoptions. Feel good place!!

We‚Äôve driven by this cat caf√© many times, and our kids have been wanting to check it out. We finally visited with six of us in our family(we are typically 8). While we appreciate that the entry fee helps support stray cats, the $8 per person charge for just 30 minutes felt excessive‚Äîespecially for a larger family. On top of that, purchasing drinks added to the overall cost, making it an expensive outing.

What made it even more disappointing was that there were only three cats out to play, and with another couple in the room, interaction was minimal. We mostly just sat and watched the cats, which we could have done from the window without paying admission.

We understand that caring for the cats requires funding, but a lower entry fee‚Äîor at least ensuring more active interaction with the cats‚Äîwould make it a better experience. If the pricing were more reasonable, we‚Äôd be happy to visit more often and support the cause. Unfortunately, at its current cost, we won‚Äôt be returning.

1st time at the Salisbury Mac Tabby location. Great place to grab a coffee and socialize with the kitties. Loved the windows for the cats and there was even a window seat for people too. The staff were friendly and helpful.

Cute cat cafe! The kitties when I went were super playful! They also have a $8/30min option (whereas other cat cafe's I've been to only have a minimum 1hr option). And they support local coffee/bakery/etc.!
First time here and I enjoyed every bit of it. Loved spending time with all the Cats on my birthday! I will definitely be back. Wish I could adopt all of them.‚ù§Ô∏è

This is a very cool place in Carthage, North Carolina. It is a coffee shop with a cat playroom attached. The playroom houses cats that are available for adoption. For a fee you can go in and play with the cats and give them treats and loves.  There were 8 cats today. This was the highlight of my granddaughter's year I think. We did not go home with a new cat but the next time we are in the market for one this will be the place we go.  The nice lady who helped us was named Wendy. She was super friendly and very knowledgeable. We will definitely return again and again.

Selecting a breeder is a huge decision. As first-timers, we wanted to make sure that we went with someone who is TICA certified, breeds award-winning cats, and uses best practices and care.

We are SO thrilled with our little Penelope. Maria truly breeds the most perfect, healthy, beautiful Scottish cats of all colors. We love our little brown teddy bear and are holding ourselves back from getting another! (just yet). Delivery was quick and seamless with a direct door-to-door drop off, even though we are a few states away.

Thank you, Maria! We couldn't be happier.
I honsetly love it bc theres cat and i holded one for too long it tryed to follow me home‚ù§Ô∏è so Heart warming  ü•∞
Maria was very welcoming and knowledgeable. The cats were fun & cuddly. We enjoyed our time and plan to come back.

Booked an hour to play with the kitties and did not disappoint! It was the best way to celebrate my birthday. The cafe is super cute, the latte was really good and very reasonably priced! The owners are the sweetest and could tell they care deeply for the cats. They had some kittens that were so playful! Please go by and support this local business even just for the coffee if you're not a cat lover.. I will be back for sure!!

We took our daughter for her birthday and it was amazing. The owner is so sweet, the coffee was amazing and it doesn‚Äôt get any better than spending time with kitty‚Äôs! It‚Äôs super clean and the adoption fee is so affordable. Highly recommend you go grab a beverage, a snack and adopt a cat!

They were absolutely amazing! My husband and I recently adopted our sweet girl from the cafe and we absolutely love her. She was a bit shy at first but has since opened up with our other cat and our dogs. We can not thank you enough for our newest addition‚ù§Ô∏è

cafes.name: Brews and Mews Cat Cafe
cafes.address: 219 N Main St, Lenoir, NC 28645, USA

text.text: Came for a friend's birthday with high expectations and was not disappointed. The Moon boba tea was delicious, and the cats made my heart melt. The cat area was a little dirty, but the rest of the cafe had a chill atmosphere that made me feel right at home. Will definitely be coming back the next time I'm in the area!

wanted to say today was such a wonderful experience! my partner and i had a great time during our 3PM appointment, and during our appointment they introduced a new cat to the room. as someone who has worked in cat cafes in the past, they are doing top tier work to take care of these cats. the cats are very sweet, very social, and i can tell the staff goes to great efforts to make all of this happen. every drink i‚Äôve gotten from here has been amazing as well, and i see why people stop in just for the drinks all the time! definitely support this business, whether it‚Äôs booking an appointment or just getting a sweet drink!

Great coffee and boba drinks and fun to watch and play with the cats. Definitely stop for drinks even if you don't like cats. You can just watch them if you don't want to play. The holiday decorations are lovely and the staff are great fun.

cafes.name: Cool Beans Cat Cafe
cafes.address: 176 S Chester St, Gastonia, NC 28052, USA

text.text:
This place is so adorable and amazing you can tell they really care about the cats and there‚Äôs some rooms that‚Äôs off limits(i believe just for the cats/employees) and it‚Äôs an amazing idea to let the cats be able to take time away if it‚Äôs crowded!!

The rules are very simple and easy to follow for their safety and all of the cats are sweet they either rubbed against my hand or gave me a kiss, some are silly about trying to get the straw to your drink. (we didn‚Äôt pick up the black kitty i think his name is Sags he hopped onto my BF to try to get his straw but we respected every rule for their safety)
I also love how you can adopt them as well, MASON MY BELOVED ILL MISS YOU FOREVER i wish i could have gotten him i love his little curly belly and his cuddliness!!

We got a hazelnut frappe and a lavender frappe and it was so yummy! The girl who helped serve us was also so sweet and informative on all their names and personalities this place is an 11/10 we‚Äôll definitely be back soon hopefully to adopt! Thank you so much :D

Amazing little cat cafe in the heart of downtown Gastonia. They have an assortment of coffee, tea, bakery items, and snacks for you to enjoy while indulging in the absolute cuteness of adoptable cats.

Summary: superb coffee, fun atmosphere, great place to chill yourself or with some friends or family!

I got a plain latte, as I usually do and it was exceptionally tasty- bold and smooth.

I stumbled on this place on the way home from a family outing and thought I‚Äôd treat everyone to a fun experience- and fun it was!

You pay a fee to get in the 3 rooms where the cats are and you must chill and pet them as they come up to you. There‚Äôs little toys if you want to try to entice them to play.

I highly recommend going here, even if you only like coffee- there‚Äôs plenty of seating away from the cats, with a book area and a table.

My family knows I‚Äôm not normally a cat fan, but I had a good time!
All in all it was a great experience and we‚Äôll certainly be back soon- me mainly for the coffee, my family mainly for the cats.

cafes.name: Whisker & Kettle Tea Room and Cat Cafe
cafes.address: 234 N Main St, Rutherfordton, NC 28139, USA

text.text: I'm so glad our little town finally got a cat cafe of a sorts! I love the kitties! It's also a nice a quiet place to read or study. The other side has beautiful tea sets to choose from. I'm totally making this place my new home now lmao.

What a delightful experience!
Spent a little time with the cats. All of them were so cute. The cat areas are well taken care of.
Afterwards we had tea for 2.
They have the cutest tea sets and you get to choose your own cup and saucer from their counter.
They had many tea options, so you're sure to find something you like.
I will surely become a regular.
By far the best cat cafe I've been to so far. Warm, clean atmosphere, inviting staff, and some of the friendliest cats I've ever met. Will definitely be coming back and bringing friends!

Rock Hill.name: Purrfect Pair Cat Cafe
Rock Hill.address: 1125 N Anderson Rd #101, Rock Hill, SC 29730, USA

text.text: We had a great time at the cat cafe. The cafe is super clean. The cats were so happy and enjoyed all of the rubs and love. The staff is super friendly and helpful with any questions asked. It‚Äôs so warm and inviting. We felt right at home. My daughter and I had an amazing time relaxing with the cats. I highly recommend the Cat Cafe if you are looking to relax and enjoy the cats.

This place is fun! The kitties are all very nice and sociable. The 30 min went by super fast. Time flies when your having fun! They have great coffee and hot chocolate too! We'll be back to pet cute cats and drink some coffee. Highly recommend!

Purrfect Pair Cat Cafe is an asset to Rock Hill. The cats are well cared for and clearly happy. The staff is friendly and treats each cat as their own. The cat lounge smells fresh and clean despite housing so many cats. The good that they are doing for the community is undeniable.
